SIMPLE: sometimes
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sometimes
<hw>Some"times`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sometime</ets> + adverbial ending <ets>-s</ets>, as in
<ets>-wards</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Formerly; sometime.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That fair and warlike form⟦br⟧
In which the majesty of buried Denmark⟦br⟧
Did <qex>sometimes</qex> march.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At times; at intervals; not always; now and then;
occasionally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is good that we <qex>sometimes</qex> be contradicted.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sometimes . . . sometimes</b></col>, <cd>at certain times
. . . at certain other times; <as>as, <ex>sometimes</ex> he is earnest,
<ex>sometimes</ex> he is frivolous</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sometimes</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sometimes
<hw>Some"times`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Former; sometime.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy <qex>sometimes</qex> brother's wife.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somewhat</ent>⟦br⟧
